# Implementation Plan: Multi-Tenant Menu Catalog Manager & Digital Menu QR Generator

This plan outlines the second phase of the SaaS Outlet Settings Hub, enabling multi-tenant menu catalog management and digital menu QR code generation.

## Proposed Changes

### Settings Hub Page
- **[MODIFY] `apps/pos/src/pages/SettingsPage.tsx`**:
  - Connect the "Menu Catalog Manager" tab to render the new `<MenuCatalogSetup />` component instead of the placeholder card.

### Menu Catalog Component
- **[NEW] `apps/pos/src/components/settings/MenuCatalogSetup.tsx`**:
  - **Real-time Master Catalog**:
    - Connects to Firestore via `onSnapshot` querying `items` collection filtered by `outlet_id`.
    - Group items dynamically by their `category` field.
    - Render item cards displaying name, price (formatted in Rupees), tax group, and status.
  - **Inline Stock Toggling**:
    - Add an active toggle switch on each card to toggle `is_available` (`true`/`false`).
    - Fires an `updateDoc` call instantly so waiter terminals (`OrderPanel.tsx`) respect availability in real time.
  - **Create/Edit Item Modal**:
    - Modal form with fields:
      - Item Name (text)
      - Category (combobox / select with option to enter a custom category)
      - Price in Rupees (converted to **paise** before sending to Firestore)
      - Tax Group ID (`tax_gst_5`, `tax_gst_18`, `tax_nil`)
      - Availability toggle
    - Saves document with `outlet_id: outletId` to enforce strict tenant isolation.
  - **Digital Menu QR Code Generator Component**:
    - Renders a card generating a pure functional QR code targeting `window.location.origin + '/#/digital-menu/' + outletId`.
    - Implemented cleanly using canvas/SVG matrix rendering (without central logos or embedded icons, keeping it pristine).
    - Includes a **"Download QR Poster"** button that extracts the high-resolution canvas/image blob for local download.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> For the QR Code generation, I will generate a pure, high-resolution QR matrix via a lightweight SVG/Canvas generator to ensure crisp rendering and instant PNG/SVG downloading without requiring heavy external NPM rebuilds. Does this approach work for you?

## Verification Plan
1. Open the "Menu Catalog Manager" tab in Outlet Settings.
2. Click "Create New Item" and add a new item with category, price in Rupees, and 5% GST tax group.
3. Verify the item appears under its designated category.
4. Toggle "Out of Stock" on an item and confirm the state updates in Firestore instantly.
5. Verify the Digital Menu QR Code card renders the pure matrix pointing to `/digital-menu/:outletId` and test the "Download QR" action.
